article.headline: Bowling Green dominates Earlham, 102-49
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- Junior Jehvon Clarke had 17 points, eight assists and six steals Saturday as Bowling Green dominated Earlham in a 102-49 victory in the season opener for both teams at the Stroh Center. Freshman Spencer Parker came off the bench in his first game as a Falcon to put up 16 points for Bowling Green with six rebounds and six assists. Starting forward Chauncey Orr was two-for-three from the 3-point line and had 14 points overall. Richaun Holmes chipped in with 12 points and a team-high eight rebounds. The Falcons had a double-digit lead at 12:00 in the first half and never looked back. They led by 20 points at halftime. Accuracy was a problem for the Quakers who were just 31 percent from the floor, shooting only 19-of-61. Earlham's top scorer, Michael Parker, had 16 points and a team-high 7 rebounds.
